Police have confirmed that a Premier League footballer has been arrested on suspicion of rape. The player is unable to be named for legal reasons, but is currently in custody and being quizzed by officers Scotland Yard have confirmed in a statement that the man was taken into custody in the early hours of Monday morning. The statement from the Met PoliceÂ read: "On 4 July, an allegation of rape of a woman in her 20s was reported to police. "It was reported the alleged rape happened in June 2022. On 4 July, a 29-year-old man was arrested at an address in Barnet on suspicion of rape and taken into custody where he remains." The club in question has declined to comment on the matter. It is not clear whether or not he will take part in their pre-season fixture schedule. 